<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê PERMA ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="page" id="perma">
  <div class="perma-hero">
    <div class="perma-inner">
      <div class="eyebrow">Seligman 2011 ¬∑ Flourish Framework</div>
      <h2 class="page-title">PERMA:<br><em>The Daily Spine</em></h2>
      <p class="page-sub">Seligman introduced PERMA in his book <em>Flourish</em> ‚Äî not coincidentally, the name of this app. Each of the five pillars runs as a daily micro-exercise mapped to the climate resilience context. The PERMA-Profiler (Butler & Kern, 2016) is administered at Weeks 1, 6, and 12 as the primary outcome measure.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="perma-grid">
    <div class="perma-card" style="border-top-color:#d4603a;">
      <div class="perma-letter" style="background:rgba(212,96,58,0.15);color:#d4603a;">P</div>
      <h4>Positive Emotion</h4>
      <div class="pm-climate">Climate application</div>
      <p>Climate grief can narrow attention and foreclose positive feeling. Rebuilding the capacity for positive emotion ‚Äî joy, awe, hope, serenity ‚Äî is not denial of crisis. It is the psychological fuel for sustained action.</p>
      <div class="pm-exercise"><strong>üåÖ Daily Exercise: Climate Awe Journal (3 min)</strong>Sunnie asks: "Find one moment of awe, beauty, or wonder connected to the living world today ‚Äî however small." Research shows awe counteracts the constricted attention of eco-anxiety and generates prosocial motivation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="perma-card" style="border-top-color:#5a8fa8;">
      <div class="perma-letter" style="background:rgba(90,143,168,0.15);color:#5a8fa8;">E</div>
      <h4>Engagement</h4>
      <div class="pm-climate">Climate application</div>
      <p>Flow ‚Äî the state of total absorption ‚Äî is both a well-being builder and a reliable sign of intrinsic motivation. The ecological activities that create flow for each user become the daily practices that sustain engagement.</p>
      <div class="pm-exercise"><strong>üåä Daily Exercise: Eco-Flow Finder (5 min)</strong>Sunnie asks: "What sustainability-related activity made time disappear this week?" Users identify and practice their eco-flow state ‚Äî their most intrinsically motivated form of climate engagement.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="perma-card" style="border-top-color:#7fb069;">
      <div class="perma-letter" style="background:rgba(127,176,105,0.15);color:#7fb069;">R</div>
      <h4>Relationships</h4>
      <div class="pm-climate">Climate application</div>
      <p>"Other people matter" (Peterson). Climate isolation is one of the most damaging dynamics for young people ‚Äî finding even one person who shares your concern changes the psychological landscape. The Climate Circles peer groups are the R anchor.</p>
      <div class="pm-exercise"><strong>ü§ù Weekly Exercise: Climate Conversation Card (10 min)</strong>A Sunnie-generated conversation starter shared with one person in your life each week. Not to convince ‚Äî to connect. Calibrated from casual to close depending on intimacy level.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="perma-card" style="border-top-color:#c4956a;">
      <div class="perma-letter" style="background:rgba(196,149,106,0.15);color:#c4956a;">M</div>
      <h4>Meaning</h4>
      <div class="pm-climate">Climate application</div>
      <p>Meaning-focused coping (Ojala & Chen, Cambridge Ch.14) is the only coping style associated with BOTH better mental health AND greater climate engagement simultaneously. Purpose is the bridge between distress and leadership.</p>
      <div class="pm-exercise"><strong>üß≠ Daily Exercise: Purpose Pulse (2 min)</strong>End-of-day Sunnie check-in: "Did today feel connected to something larger? Rate 1‚Äì10." Flags when meaning drops below 5 for 3 consecutive days and triggers a meaning-recovery practice.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="perma-card" style="border-top-color:#7a5aa8;">
      <div class="perma-letter" style="background:rgba(122,90,168,0.15);color:#7a5aa8;">A</div>
      <h4>Accomplishment</h4>
      <div class="pm-climate">Climate application</div>
      <p>Self-efficacy ‚Äî the belief that your actions matter ‚Äî is the strongest predictor of sustained pro-environmental behavior. Building accomplishment through small, visible wins creates the momentum for larger ones.</p>
      <div class="pm-exercise"><strong>üèÜ Weekly Exercise: Eco-Achievement Log</strong>Every Sunday, log one sustainability-related accomplishment ‚Äî however small. Displayed as a visual timeline. Regular acknowledgment of small wins builds the self-efficacy needed to attempt larger ones.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="perma-card" style="border-top-color:linear-gradient(90deg,#d4603a,#5a8fa8);">
      <div class="perma-letter" style="background:rgba(127,176,105,0.1);color:var(--fern);font-size:0.9rem;">ALL</div>
      <h4>Weekly PERMA Check-In</h4>
      <div class="pm-climate">Sunnie ¬∑ Every Sunday ¬∑ 5 min</div>
      <p>Five questions (one per pillar, rated 0‚Äì10) build your weekly PERMA profile. When a domain drops, Sunnie offers a targeted repair activity. Full PERMA-Profiler (Butler & Kern) at Weeks 1, 6, and 12.</p>
      <div class="pm-exercise"><strong>üìä Measurement</strong>The PERMA-Profiler uses 15 validated items (3 per domain). Validated for youth populations ‚Äî PMC Qatar study, N=502 ages 13‚Äì18. Primary outcome measure for the blind study protocol.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê CAN FRAMEWORK ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="page" id="can">
  <div class="can-hero">
    <div class="can-inner">
      <div class="can-eyebrow">Stanford ¬∑ Novy, Banerjee & Matson 2021 ¬∑ SUST 220</div>
      <h2>Connect. Adapt.<br><em>Innovate.</em></h2>
      <p class="can-desc">Julia Novy's CAN framework ‚Äî the core of Stanford's Change Leadership for Sustainability program ‚Äî identifies three orientations that define effective sustainability leaders. Purpose sits at the center of the triangle, anchoring all three. In this curriculum, CAN becomes a dedicated 3-week arc (Weeks 7‚Äì9) ‚Äî the pivot where inner healing becomes outer leadership.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CAN TRIANGLE -->
  <div style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto 3rem;padding:0 2rem;">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 400 360" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="width:100%;height:auto;">
      <!-- Glow defs -->
      <defs>
        <radialGradient id="bgGlow" cx="50%" cy="55%" r="50%">
