      <text x="370" y="332" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(252,211,77,0.7)" font-family="DM Sans, sans-serif" font-size="8" letter-spacing="2">INNOVATE</text>

      <!-- Center ‚Äî Purpose -->
      <circle cx="200" cy="192" r="48" fill="rgba(13,26,13,0.95)" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,0.12)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
      <circle cx="200" cy="192" r="44" fill="none" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,0.06)" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="200" y="186" text-anchor="middle" fill="white" font-family="serif" font-size="13" font-weight="900" font-style="italic">Purpose</text>
      <text x="200" y="200" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.35)" font-family="DM Sans, sans-serif" font-size="7" letter-spacing="1.5">YOUR VALUES</text>
      <text x="200" y="212" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.35)" font-family="DM Sans, sans-serif" font-size="7" letter-spacing="1.5">IN ACTION</text>

      <!-- Week labels on edges -->
      <text x="102" y="155" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(59,130,246,0.45)" font-family="DM Mono, monospace" font-size="7" letter-spacing="1">Week 7</text>
      <text x="298" y="155" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(245,158,11,0.45)" font-family="DM Mono, monospace" font-size="7" letter-spacing="1">Week 9</text>
      <text x="200" y="342" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(139,92,246,0.45)" font-family="DM Mono, monospace" font-size="7" letter-spacing="1">Week 8</text>
    </svg>
    <p style="text-align:center;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);margin-top:0.5rem;">CAN Framework ¬∑ Novy, Banerjee & Matson ¬∑ Stanford 2021</p>
  </div>

  <!-- CAN explanation -->
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 1.5rem;margin-bottom:2rem;">
    <p style="font-size:0.87rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);line-height:1.8;max-width:680px;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">The triangle's geometry is intentional. Purpose ‚Äî your ecological values, your "why" ‚Äî sits at the center. Each orientation draws from it and feeds back into it. You cannot genuinely Connect without knowing your purpose. You cannot Adapt without purpose anchoring you through uncertainty. You cannot Innovate without purpose directing what you build toward. The New Leader develops all three orientations simultaneously, with purpose as the stable center.</p>
    <div style="background:rgba(245,158,11,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(245,158,11,0.15);border-radius:10px;padding:1.25rem;">
      <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);line-height:1.75;"><strong style="color:rgba(245,158,11,0.8);">Source:</strong> Novy, Banerjee & Matson (2021) used empathy interviews with 100+ sustainability leaders from business, government, and civil society to identify what New Leaders actually need. Stanford's SUST 220 course description states: <em style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);">"The course teaches students the Connect, Adapt and Innovate (CAN) orientations and other skills which enhance students' ability to cultivate resilience and well-being in their lives and to lead change in complex systems."</em></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CAN 3 cards -->
  <div class="can-cards">
    <div class="can-card">
      <div class="can-card-letter" style="background:#3b82f6;">C</div>
      <h3>Connect</h3>
      <div class="can-card-week">Week 7 ¬∑ PERMA: R + P</div>
      <p>Build bridges across difference. Connect with those who hold different perspectives, positions, and power. The New Leader must be "highly collaborative and inclusive" ‚Äî capable of deep listening, empathy, and genuine inquiry. Connection also means reconnecting with the natural world and with your own ecological identity.</p>
      <div class="can-card-acts">
        <div class="can-act-mini" style="border-color:#3b82f6;">
          <h6>üëÇ Radical Listening Challenge</h6>
          <p>One empathy interview with someone who holds a different climate perspective. Goal: understand, not persuade. Report what surprised you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="can-act-mini" style="border-color:#3b82f6;">
          <h6>üåâ Stakeholder Map</h6>
          <p>Map 5‚Äì8 stakeholders in your climate issue. What does each value? Where do values overlap with yours?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="can-act-mini" style="border-color:#3b82f6;">
          <h6>üî• Climate Circle Peer Witnessing</h6>
          <p>Share your leverage point and one honest fear. Others witness without advice. Radical connection in 30 minutes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="can-card">
      <div class="can-card-letter" style="background:#8b5cf6;">A</div>
      <h3>Adapt</h3>
      <div class="can-card-week">Week 8 ¬∑ PERMA: E + A</div>
      <p>Embrace uncertainty, iterate, pivot. The New Leader has "capacity to understand change, be adaptable, and embrace ambiguity." Adaptation is not giving up ‚Äî it is the intelligence to keep moving when the path changes. Resilience reservoirs are built in this week so the Innovate week doesn't deplete them.</p>
      <div class="can-card-acts">
        <div class="can-act-mini" style="border-color:#8b5cf6;">
          <h6>üîÅ Fail Forward Challenge</h6>
          <p>Run one climate micro-experiment this week. Report back. Extract the learning. Normalizes iteration over perfection.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="can-act-mini" style="border-color:#8b5cf6;">
          <h6>üîÆ Three Futures Exercise</h6>
          <p>Map pessimistic, business-as-usual, and transformative futures for your issue. What small things nudge toward the transformative?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="can-act-mini" style="border-color:#8b5cf6;">
          <h6>üîã Resilience Reservoir</h6>
          <p>Visual map of what fills vs. drains your capacity. Sunnie monitors levels and flags depletion before burnout.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="can-card">
      <div class="can-card-letter" style="background:#f59e0b;">I</div>
      <h3>Innovate</h3>
      <div class="can-card-week">Week 9 ¬∑ PERMA: M + A peak</div>
      <p>Create new possibilities. "Creative confidence in the face of daunting challenges, risk-taking, bias for action." Innovation in this context is not a tech product ‚Äî it is any values-aligned creation that didn't exist before: a program, a conversation series, a partnership, a community initiative.</p>
      <div class="can-card-acts">
        <div class="can-act-mini" style="border-color:#f59e0b;">
          <h6>üí° Climate Innovation Brief</h6>
          <p>Design one values-aligned, achievable innovation using your identity, leverage point, stakeholder map, and scenario work as raw material.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="can-act-mini" style="border-color:#f59e0b;">
          <h6>üé§ Pitch Your Innovation</h6>
          <p>3-minute pitch to your Climate Circle. Practice making an idea legible and compelling to others. Peer feedback collected.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="can-act-mini" style="border-color:#f59e0b;">
          <h6>üåç The One Real Thing</h6>
          <p>One public commitment: the first concrete step, with a date, witnessed by your Climate Circle. Social commitment + values alignment = highest efficacy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sunnie-box">
    <div class="sunnie-label">üí¨ Sunnie across the CAN Arc</div>
    <div class="sunnie-line"><strong>Week 7 ‚Äî Connect:</strong> This week I want you to do something uncomfortable: have a real conversation with someone who sees climate differently from you. Not to change their mind. Just to understand it. What you learn will likely surprise you ‚Äî and it'll make you a better leader.</div>
    <div class="sunnie-line"><strong>Week 8 ‚Äî Adapt:</strong> The best innovators know: the first version is supposed to be wrong. This week we run a micro-experiment ‚Äî small enough to do, meaningful enough to learn from. Failing fast is the strategy, not the failure.</div>
    <div class="sunnie-line"><strong>Week 9 ‚Äî Innovate:</strong> You've spent nine weeks building something. Your values. Your leverage point. Your connections. Your resilience. Now I want to ask: what does everything you've built actually point toward? What wants to be created?</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê MODULES ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="page" id="modules">
<div class="container">
  <div class="slabel">12-Week Curriculum</div>
  <h2 class="page-title">Six Modules.<br><em>Three Arcs.</em></h2>
  <p class="page-sub">The curriculum moves through Healing (Weeks 1‚Äì4), Rooting (Weeks 5‚Äì6), and Leading (Weeks 7‚Äì12). CEDAR scores personalize pacing. CAN runs Weeks 7‚Äì9 as the action pivot. PERMA runs daily throughout.</p>

  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:1rem;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
    <!-- M1 -->
    <div style="background:var(--surface);border-radius:12px;padding:1.4rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-top:3px solid var(--clay);">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.58rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--clay);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Module I ¬∑ Weeks 1‚Äì2 ¬∑ Healing</div>
      <h4 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Identity: Who Am I in Relation to the Earth?</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.79rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);line-height:1.65;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Ecological identity narrative. PERMA baseline. Developmental psychoeducation. Values map. The Stanford New Leader model begins here ‚Äî identity is the inner ring.</p>
      <div style="font-size:0.7rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.25);">Stanford Ring 1 ¬∑ Cambridge Ch.3‚Äì4 ¬∑ CEDAR: Affect</div>
    </div>
    <!-- M2 -->
    <div style="background:var(--surface);border-radius:12px;padding:1.4rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-top:3px solid var(--fern);">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.58rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--fern);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Module II ¬∑ Week 3 ¬∑ Healing</div>
      <h4 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Perspective: Systems Thinking Without Drowning</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.79rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);line-height:1.65;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Leverage point mapping. ACT defusion from doom-scrolling. Emergence scan. Uncertainty tolerance. Systems thinking taught therapeutically ‚Äî to find agency, not catalog catastrophe.</p>
      <div style="font-size:0.7rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.25);">Stanford Ring 2 ¬∑ Cambridge Ch.8 ¬∑ CEDAR: Cognitive</div>
    </div>
    <!-- M3 -->
    <div style="background:var(--surface);border-radius:12px;padding:1.4rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-top:3px solid var(--sky);">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.58rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--sky);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Module III ¬∑ Week 4 ¬∑ Healing</div>
      <h4 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Clinical Foundations: The Full Spectrum of Distress</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.79rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);line-height:1.65;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Distress spectrum self-location. Neuroscience of eco-anxiety. Dissociation awareness. Psychoanalytic reflection. Users who locate themselves make better support decisions.</p>
      <div style="font-size:0.7rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.25);">Cambridge Ch.3‚Äì8 ¬∑ CEDAR: all 4 dimensions</div>
    </div>
    <!-- M4 -->
    <div style="background:var(--surface);border-radius:12px;padding:1.4rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-top:3px solid var(--fern);">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.58rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--fern);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Module IV ¬∑ Weeks 5‚Äì6 ¬∑ Rooting</div>
      <h4 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Capability: Regulate, Root, Restore</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.79rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);line-height:1.65;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Secure base mapping. Nature observation (daily 5 min). Creative expression. Intersectional climate justice. Climate Circles begin. ACT, ecotherapy, and psychodynamic interventions.</p>
      <div style="font-size:0.7rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.25);">Stanford Ring 3 ¬∑ Cambridge Ch.10‚Äì11 ¬∑ CEDAR: Social</div>
    </div>
    <!-- M5 -->
    <div style="background:var(--surface);border-radius:12px;padding:1.4rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-top:3px solid var(--clay);">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.58rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--clay);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Module V ¬∑ Week 6 ¬∑ Rooting ‚Üí Bridge</div>
      <h4 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Meaning: From Paralysis to Purpose</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.79rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);line-height:1.65;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Meaning excavation. Constructive hope. PERMA mid-point. Activism Balance Sheet. The empirical bridge between healing and leadership. PERMA Meaning scores typically peak here.</p>
      <div style="font-size:0.7rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.25);">Cambridge Ch.14 (Ojala & Chen) ¬∑ CEDAR: Motivation</div>
    </div>
    <!-- M6 -->
    <div style="background:var(--surface);border-radius:12px;padding:1.4rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-top:3px solid rgba(245,158,11,0.6);">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.58rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#f59e0b;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Module VI ¬∑ Weeks 10‚Äì12 ¬∑ Leading</div>
      <h4 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Agency: Leading Change in Complex Systems</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.79rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);line-height:1.65;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Sphere of systems influence. Innovation reviews. PERMA endline. Intergenerational letter. The Stanford Agency ring ‚Äî where identity, perspective, and capability become directed action.</p>
      <div style="font-size:0.7rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.25);">Stanford Ring 4 ¬∑ Cambridge Ch.15‚Äì16 ¬∑ CEDAR: all 4</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>

<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê JOURNEY ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="page" id="journey">
<div class="container">
  <div class="slabel">Week by Week</div>
  <h2 class="page-title">The 12-Week<br><em>Journey</em></h2>
  <p class="page-sub">Daily micro-practices (5‚Äì8 min) anchor each week. One deeper weekly practice (20‚Äì30 min). PERMA tracked weekly. CAN arc runs Weeks 7‚Äì9. CEDAR re-assessed at Weeks 6 and 12.</p>
  <div class="journey-wrap" style="padding:0;">
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle">1</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod">Module I ¬∑ Identity ¬∑ Healing</div><h4>The Earth That Made You + CEDAR Baseline</h4><p>CEDAR assessment Day 1. PERMA-Profiler baseline. Eco-identity narrative. Values map.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag cedar">CEDAR Baseline</span><span class="wtag">Eco-Identity</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle">2</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod">Module I ¬∑ Identity ¬∑ Healing</div><h4>Justice, Anger & What You Inherited</h4><p>Intergenerational justice. Anger validation. Climate Conversation Card (R) launched. Daily Eco-Flow Finder (E).</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag">Generational Justice</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle">3</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod">Module II ¬∑ Systems ¬∑ Healing</div><h4>Seeing the System ‚Äî Finding the Door</h4><p>Leverage Point Map. ACT defusion. Emergence scan. Uncertainty tolerance practice.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag">Leverage Map</span><span class="wtag">ACT</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle">4</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod">Module III ¬∑ Clinical ¬∑ Healing</div><h4>Naming What's Happening Inside</h4><p>Distress spectrum. Neuroscience psychoeducation. Dissociation awareness. Weekly PERMA check-in begins.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag">Distress Spectrum</span><span class="wtag cedar">CEDAR Review</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle">5</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod">Module IV ¬∑ Capability ¬∑ Rooting</div><h4>Roots and Secure Bases</h4><p>Secure Base Map. Nature observation daily (5 min). Creative expression. Climate Circles begin.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag">Secure Base</span><span class="wtag">Ecotherapy</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle">6</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod">Module V ¬∑ Meaning ¬∑ Bridge ‚Üí CAN</div><h4>From Paralysis to Purpose + Mid-Point</h4><p>CEDAR re-assessment. PERMA-Profiler mid-point. Meaning excavation. Constructive hope. Activism Balance Sheet.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag cedar">CEDAR Mid-Point</span><span class="wtag can">‚Üí CAN Begins</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle can-week">7</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod" style="color:#3b82f6;">CAN ¬∑ CONNECT ¬∑ Leading</div><h4>Radical Listening + Stakeholder Map</h4><p>Empathy interview challenge. Multi-stakeholder map. Climate Circle peer witnessing session.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag can">CONNECT Week</span><span class="wtag can">Empathy Interview</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle can-week" style="color:#8b5cf6;border-color:rgba(139,92,246,0.4);background:rgba(139,92,246,0.1);">8</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod" style="color:#8b5cf6;">CAN ¬∑ ADAPT ¬∑ Leading</div><h4>Fail Forward + Scenario Planning</h4><p>Micro-experiment run and debriefed. Three Futures. Resilience Reservoir check.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag can">ADAPT Week</span><span class="wtag can">Rapid Prototype</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle can-week" style="color:#f59e0b;">9</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod" style="color:#f59e0b;">CAN ¬∑ INNOVATE ¬∑ Leading</div><h4>Climate Innovation Brief + Pitch</h4><p>Innovation brief designed. 3-min pitch to Climate Circle. One Real Thing commitment made publicly.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag can">INNOVATE Week</span><span class="wtag can">Innovation Brief</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle cap-week">10</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod">Module VI ¬∑ Agency ¬∑ Leading</div><h4>Systems of Influence + Innovation Review</h4><p>Sphere of Systems map. Climate Circle: innovation first-step reviews. Day 15 follow-up.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag">Systems Map</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle cap-week">11</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod">Module VI ¬∑ Agency ¬∑ Leading</div><h4>Sustaining the Work</h4><p>Burnout prevention. Innovation Day 30 follow-up. Intergenerational Letter draft begun.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag">Burnout Prevention</span></div></div></div>
    <div class="week-row"><div class="week-num-col"><div class="wnum-circle cap-week" style="border-color:rgba(127,176,105,0.6);color:var(--fern);">12</div></div><div class="week-content-col"><div class="week-mod">Capstone ¬∑ Graduation</div><h4>Letter to What Comes Next + Full Endline</h4><p>CEDAR endline. PERMA-Profiler endline. Intergenerational Letter completed. Climate Circle closing ceremony. Graduation.</p><div class="wtags"><span class="wtag cedar">CEDAR Endline</span><span class="wtag">PERMA Endline</span><span class="wtag">Graduation</span></div></div></div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>

<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê EVIDENCE ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="page" id="evidence">
<div class="container">
  <div class="slabel">Academic Sources</div>
  <h2 class="page-title">Evidence Base</h2>
  <p class="page-sub">Every activity is traceable to peer-reviewed research. Primary sources anchor the architecture; supporting sources cross-validate specific practices.</p>
  <div class="ev-list">
    <div class="ev-card" style="border-left-color:var(--ember);">
      <div class="ev-type">Primary ¬∑ MHCCA / Simon Fraser University</div>
      <h4>CEDAR ‚Äî Climate-related Ecological Distress and Resilience Scale</h4>
      <p>The Climate Reactions Self-Assessment Tool developed by researchers at SFU and published by the Mental Health and Climate Change Alliance. 12 validated items across 4 dimensions: Affect & Emotional Response, Cognitive & Social Impairment, Social Support & Resource Access, Motivation & Behavioural Engagement. The only validated climate-specific distress AND resilience tool currently available. Dropout recommendations drawn directly from the MHCCA dimension guides.</p>
      <div class="ev-used">Assessment engine for the entire curriculum. Personalization layer for Sunnie recommendations.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ev-card" style="border-left-color:var(--clay);">
      <div class="ev-type">Primary ¬∑ Stanford University ¬∑ MDPI Sustainability 2021</div>
      <h4>Novy, Banerjee & Matson ‚Äî "A Core Curriculum for Sustainability Leadership"</h4>
      <p>Foundational paper for Stanford's Change Leadership for Sustainability Program. Introduces the New Leader four-ring model (Identity ‚Üí Perspective ‚Üí Capability ‚Üí Agency) and the CAN orientations (Connect, Adapt, Innovate) as the core of SUST 220. The paper's 100+ empathy interviews with global sustainability leaders validate the CAN framework against real-world practitioner need. Purpose as the center of the CAN triangle reflects the program's explicit normative goal of intergenerational well-being.</p>
      <div class="ev-used">CAN triangle framework. New Leader identity model. All six module arc structure.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ev-card" style="border-left-color:var(--fern);">
      <div class="ev-type">Primary ¬∑ Cambridge University Press 2024</div>
      <h4>Haase & Hudson (eds.) ‚Äî "Climate Change and Youth Mental Health: Multidisciplinary Perspectives"</h4>
      <p>Most comprehensive clinical text on youth climate distress. Ch.3‚Äì8: psychiatric, developmental, neurobiological, psychoanalytic, trauma, and CBT foundations. Ch.10: ACT, psychodynamic, and ecotherapy for climate distress. Ch.11: intersectional and ecological perspectives. Ch.14 (Ojala & Chen): meaning-focused coping as the dual-outcome coping strategy. Ch.15: social-ecological systems framework. Appendix B: Costs and Benefits of Activism Scale.</p>
      <div class="ev-used">Clinical backbone for all modules. Distress spectrum. Meaning-focused coping evidence. Intergenerational framework.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ev-card" style="border-left-color:var(--sky);">
      <div class="ev-type">Primary ¬∑ Positive Psychology ¬∑ Seligman 2011</div>
      <h4>Seligman, M.E.P. ‚Äî "Flourish: A Visionary New Understanding of Happiness and Well-being"</h4>
      <p>Introduces PERMA (Positive Emotion, Engagement, Relationships, Meaning, Accomplishment) as the framework for flourishing. Not coincidentally, the basis for this app's name. Each pillar mapped to a daily climate-specific micro-exercise. PERMA-Profiler (Butler & Kern, 2016) provides the primary outcome measure. The distinction between PERMA as a framework rather than a theory allows flexible, contextual application to climate resilience.</p>
      <div class="ev-used">Daily micro-exercise spine. PERMA-Profiler as primary outcome measure for blind study.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ev-card" style="border-left-color:var(--ember);">
      <div class="ev-type">Supporting ¬∑ ScienceDirect 2023</div>
      <h4>Lindqvist et al. ‚Äî Climate-Specific Internet CBT Randomized Controlled Trial</h4>
      <p>The only published RCT on internet-delivered CBT for climate distress. Effect sizes: depression d=0.87, stress d=0.76, quality of life d=0.79 over 8 weeks. ICBT participants also showed increased pro-environmental behavior post-treatment. Validates the digital delivery model and provides effect size benchmarks for power calculations in a future blind study. Critical finding: treating distress can increase climate engagement, not decrease it.</p>
      <div class="ev-used">Delivery model validation. Blind study power calculation basis. Effect size benchmarks.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ev-card" style="border-left-color:var(--fern);">
      <div class="ev-type">Supporting ¬∑ PMC 2021</div>
      <h4>Baudon & Jachens ‚Äî Scoping Review of Eco-Anxiety Interventions</h4>
      <p>Reviews 34 records. Five major intervention categories: resilience-building, action-encouraging, social connection, nature connection, grief-informed approaches. Creative expression, grief rituals, and group peer support are evidence-supported. The CEDAR Social dimension activities draw directly from the social connection and nature connection recommendations.</p>
      <div class="ev-used">Cross-validates Modules I, III, IV, VI activities.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ev-card" style="border-left-color:var(--sky);">
      <div class="ev-type">Supporting ¬∑ Taylor & Francis 2024</div>
      <h4>Terrien & Brouillard ‚Äî ACT for Climate-Induced Psychological Distress</h4>
      <p>Establishes ACT's six core processes as directly applicable to eco-anxiety. Specifically cultivates "psychological self-care that prevents climate fatigue or burnout" ‚Äî a critical function given the CAN arc's demands. ACT defusion (Module II), values clarification (Module I), and committed action (Module V and CAN Innovate week) all validated.</p>
      <div class="ev-used">ACT-based activities across Modules I, II, V and the CAN arc.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ev-card" style="border-left-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);">
      <div class="ev-type">Supporting ¬∑ PMC 2025</div>
      <h4>Qatar Youth Study ‚Äî PERMA Validation in Adolescents</h4>
      <p>N=502 high school students (ages 13‚Äì18). Validates PERMA-Profiler for youth populations. Finds anxiety and depression negatively associated with PERMA scores, confirming PERMA as a sensitive measure for detecting both distress and resilience in the target population of this curriculum.</p>
      <div class="ev-used">Validates PERMA-Profiler use with youth. Blind study measurement justification.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>

<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê JS ‚ïê‚ïê -->
<!-- ‚ïê‚ïê CLASSIC VIEW ‚ïê‚ïê -->
<div class="page" id="classic">
  <div style="background:var(--surface);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding:1rem 1.5rem;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;">
    <div>
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--fern);margin-bottom:0.2rem;">Classic View ¬∑ v3 Build</div>
      <p style="font-size:0.8rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.4);">The full v3 curriculum ‚Äî PERMA, CAN, Modules I‚ÄìVI, Journey, Blind Study, Evidence ‚Äî preserved exactly as built.</p>
    </div>
    <a href="flourish_v3_classic.html" target="_blank" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.4rem;background:var(--fern);color:#0d1a0d;padding:0.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:8px;font-weight:700;font-size:0.8rem;text-decoration:none;flex-shrink:0;">Open Full Screen ‚Üó</a>
  </div>
  <iframe src="flourish_v3_classic.html" style="width:100%;height:calc(100vh - 110px);border:none;display:block;" title="Flourish v3 Classic View"></iframe>
